## 5. Ignore capitalization and case-only differences
Capitalization or letter case alone must not be treated as an error.

Examples:
- `yogesh` vs `Yogesh`
- `PERRY` vs `Perry`
- `jErry` vs `Jerry`

If the only difference is case style, then:
- `flag` must be `false`
- `reason` must be `""`
- corrected values must remain exactly the same as the input values

Do not mark a name as incorrect only because it is uppercase, lowercase, title case, or mixed case.
